#How to install postgress cmd ?
1.Update Package List:
   .Open the terminal and run 
   --> sudo apt update

2. Install PostgreSQL and psql:
  .Install PostgreSQL and its tools by running
  --> sudo apt install postgresql postgresql-contrib

3. Verify Installation:
   .Check if psql is installed by typing
   --> psql --version

4. Using psql:
   .To access the PostgreSQL command-line tool, run:
  ---> sudo -u postgres psql

5. Enable PostgreSQL to Start on Boot:
  ---> sudo systemctl enable postgresql
  --> sudo systemctl start postgresql    

#How to using psql after installation ?
1. Connect to the Database:
 .Use the following command to connect to a PostgreSQL database:
 --->psql -U your_username -d your_database_name
   or 
---> sudo -u postgres psql

2. Basic Commands in psql:
  i).To list all databases:
  --> \l
  ii) To connect to a specific database:
  --> \c your_database_name
  iii) To list all tables in the current database:
   --> \dt
  iv) To quit psql:
  --->\q



